		"description": {
			"chat": "",
			"unidentified": "",
			"value": "<div class=\"spell-description\">\n  <p>\n      <strong>School:</strong>&nbsp;evocation&nbsp;[cold];\n    <br>\n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    <br>\n    <strong>Components:</strong>&nbsp;V, S<br>\n    \n      <strong>Casting Time:</strong>&nbsp;1 round<br>\n    <strong>Range:</strong>&nbsp;300 feet<br>\n    <strong>Area:</strong>&nbsp;20-ft.-radius hemisphere burst\n<br>\n    \n    \n    <strong>Duration:</strong>&nbsp;Instantaneous<br>\n    \n        <strong>Saving Throw:</strong>&nbsp;Reflex half\n\n        <br>\n        <strong>Spell Resistance:</strong>&nbsp;yes<br>\n  </p>\n  <h2>Description</h2>\n  \n\n<p>When this spell is cast, enemies within range are dealt 10d6 points of cold damage. However, up to twenty of those victims that perish as a result of this blast are then instantly animated as Medium skeleton. These skeleton serve the character indefinitely. The character cannot exceed the normal limit for controlling undead through use of this spell, but other means that allow the character to exceed the normal limit for controlled undead work just as well with undead created with <i>animus blast</i>.\n</p>\n<hr/>\n\n\n\n</div>\n"
